&lt;p&gt;Supernal is an Advanced Air Mobility (AAM) company that’s developing an electric vertical take-off and landing (eVTOL) vehicle and the ground-to-air ecosystem to support the emerging industry. By creating a sustainable, integrated, and human-centered ecosystem, we are committed to taking a thoughtful and responsible approach to entering the AAM market with a product that meets the high level of safety and reliability in today’s air transportation system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The future of mobility starts with people. We believe in creative thinking and collaboration to help build a better mobility experience for everyone, improving people’s ability to move – whether for work or play. Join our dynamic team as we strive to be a part of something greater where potential powers tomorrow!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supernal provides an inviting open-space workplace designed to foster collaboration, which aligns with one of our core values. This position is required to work on-site 5 days a week.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Supernal, we are working on new eVTOL technology to make the world a better place with Urban Air Mobility (UAM). The Sr. Manager, Mechanical and Flight Systems Engineering (M&amp;amp;FS) is responsible for guiding the development and certification of innovative dynamic systems (rotors, gearboxes), airframe, materials &amp;amp; processes, avionics, actuation, landing gear, cockpit controls, and interiors designs to achieve functional and performance requirements. The department supports the complete life cycle of associated components: requirements, concept development, engineering integration, prelim and final design and analysis, manufacturing start-up, testing, qualification, certification, production and in-service support. The role works with team members across Supernal and externally on cutting edge technologies including rotor design, composite manufacturing, and advanced structural analysis to meet safety, quality, cost, schedule, and people goals. Our ideal candidate has significant experience and expertise in FAA certificated development programs. This role will report to the CTO.&lt;/p&gt;
